node.text:
Being referred to as an “Olympian” is something I never imagined growing up. I never watched my idols and role models compete to have a chance to win a gold medal, and it’s a thought I never had until 5-6 years ago. The @olympics this week (even with all the bizarre protocols) exceeded my expectations and somehow made me want to grind and compete even harder. 

It’s an honor and a privilege to be able to represent and play for @teamusa. To put on the red white and blue is something I don’t take lightly, and enjoy the opportunity to represent my country that I love so much, playing a sport that I care so much about. Although the week is determined on how you as an individual play, the week as a whole is bigger than you and you’re not just representing yourself. You’re representing your entire country 🇺🇸

The entire staff for @usagolf deserves medals of their own. The years and time spent to get ready, make the week as easy as possible for us, was something we will never understand. But I can’t thank everybody enough for their work and all of this (especially this year during COVID), could not have been done without them.

It wasn’t the week I wanted golf wise, but we’re getting really close to some great golf. A big congrats to Xander, Sabbo, and CT for earning their medals this week. Something I look forward to being a part of down the road. One thing you’ll never be able to take from me… is I’ll always be an Olympian. Still feels weird to even type!!! 

Apologies for the novel and for the rant, but had a lot of thoughts and feelings about the week… and that’s what social media is for, right? For now, onto Memphis next week to try and defend at the @wgcfedex! LFG 💪

node.text: Can’t beat a stroll up 18 @theopen! @royalst.georges is awesome. Lots of undulation in the fairways and bizarre greens. Last major of the year… might as well make it a great one 👊🏽

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Justin Thomas in Genesis Scottish Open with @titleist, and @footjoy. May be an image of golf, nature, golf course and grass.

node.text: Thanks @scottish_open for a great week! And always to @europeantour for having us. Game is trending nicely for next week 💪
